data.enText: to kill sb, especially as a legal punishment

data.chText: 这些犯人已由行刑队枪决。
data.enText: The prisoners were executed by firing squad.
to do a piece of work, perform a duty, put a plan into action, etc.

data.chText: 他们制订并实施了一项降低燃料消耗的计划。
data.enText: They drew up and executed a plan to reduce fuel consumption.

data.chText: 这一犯罪活动实施得非常巧妙。
data.enText: The crime was very cleverly executed.

data.chText: 检查一下计算机是否已执行指令。
data.enText: Check that the computer has executed your commands.

data.chText: 成功地完成（技巧或动作）
data.enText: to successfully perform a skilful action or movement

data.chText: 飞行员完成了一个非常娴熟的着陆动作。
data.enText: The pilot executed a perfect landing.
to make or produce a work of art

data.chText: 毕加索还在奥尔塔─德圣胡安画了几幅风景画。
data.enText: Picasso also executed several landscapes at Horta de San Juan.

data.chText: 执行（法令）；使（法律文件）生效
data.enText: to follow the instructions in a legal document; to make a document legally valid

means: 成功地完成(技巧或动作)

ex.chText: 那个急诊手术是什么时候做的？
ex.enText: When was that emergency operation performed?

ex.chText: 专家对调查数据进行了分析。
ex.enText: Experts performed an analysis of the survey data.

synonyms.bx: 尤指做困难或有用的事情。

ex.chText: 她认为进行调查是搜集所需信息的最好方式。
ex.enText: In her opinion, conducting a survey is the best way to collect the information needed.

ex.chText: 他想知道如何进行科学实验。
ex.enText: He wanted to know how to conduct science experiments.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为获取信息或证实某事而进行某一活动或过程。

ex.chText: 他们正在实施一个护理计划。
ex.enText: They are executing a nursing care plan.

ex.chText: 这一秘密计划实施得很巧妙。
ex.enText: The plot was very cleverly executed.

ex.chText: 成员国必须履行条约所规定的义务。
ex.enText: It is necessary for the member states to fulfil their obligations under the treaty.

ex.chText: 作为一名教师，恪尽职守很重要。
ex.enText: As a teacher, it is important for you to fulfil your role.

ex.chText: 这些设备未能符合安全要求。
ex.enText: These pieces of equipment failed to fulfil safety requirements.

synonyms.bx: 指做要求或必须做的事情，如履行职责、义务等；也可指满足必要或应有的条件或要求，如达到标准等。

tr: sign in the presence of witnesses

example: execute the decision of the people

tr: carry out or perform an action
example: John did the painting, the weeding, and he cleaned out the gutters
the skater executed a triple pirouette

tr: kill as a means of socially sanctioned punishment
example: In some states, criminals are executed
The Mafioso who collaborated with the police was executed

tr: carry out a process or program, as on a computer or a machine
example: run a new program on the Mac
execute a will or a deed

value.def: To execute someone means to kill them as a punishment for a serious crime.

example.ex: He was executed by lethal injection earlier today...
example.tran: 他于今天早些时候被注射处死。

example.ex: One group claimed to have executed the American hostage...
example.tran: 一个组织声称已经处决了那名美国人质。

example.ex: This boy's father had been executed for conspiring against the throne.
example.tran: 这个男孩的父亲因为密谋反对君主而被处死。

example.ex: Execution by lethal injection is scheduled for July 30th.
example.tran: 定于7月30日执行注射死刑。

value.def: If you execute a plan, you carry it out.

example.ex: We are going to execute our campaign plan to the letter.
example.tran: 我们将严格施行我们的竞选计划。

example.ex: US forces are fully prepared for the execution of any action once the order is given by the president.
example.tran: 美国军队充分准备好随时执行总统的任何指令。

value.def: If you execute a difficult action or movement, you successfully perform it.

example.ex: I executed the hairpin turn high on the sheer western face of the mountains...
example.tran: 我在山脉西侧陡峭的高处成功地急转弯。

value.def: When someone executes a work of art, they make or produce it, using an idea as a basis.

example.ex: Morris executed a suite of twelve drawings in 1978...
example.tran: 莫里斯在1978年创作了由12幅画组成的一组作品。

example.ex: A well-executed shot of a tall ship is a joy to behold.
example.tran: 欣赏优秀的高桅横帆船摄影作品是种乐趣。

example.ex: The ideas in the show's presentation were good, but failed in execution.
example.tran: 那场展览陈述的想法很好，但是没能实现。
